import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='year', y='net_generation', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of net generation over the years?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.groupby(['source'])['net_generation'].sum().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='source', y='net_generation', data=data)
    chart.set_title('What is the total net generation by source?', wrap=True)
    chart.set_xlabel('Source')
    chart.set_ylabel('Net Generation')
    for index, row in data.iterrows():
        chart.text(row.name,row.net_generation, round(row.net_generation,2), color='black', ha="center")
    return chart

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    chart = sns.barplot(x='source', y='net_generation', data=data, ci=None)
    chart.set_title('What is the average net generation by source?', wrap=True)
    chart.axhline(y=data['net_generation'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['net_generation'].mean():.2f}")
    chart.legend()
    return chart

chart = plot(data)
